2. THE SOVEREIGNTY CLAUSE
   No entity, including but not limited to massive technology conglomerates 
   (e.g., Microsoft, Google, Meta, Apple), may co-opt this architecture 
   to build closed-source, proprietary operating systems that lock users 
   out of their own hardware. Any cloud or network deployment of this 
   system triggers the AGPLv3 network interaction clause, requiring full 
   source code disclosure.

3. THE KINGDOM SHIELD
   You may not disable or bypass the built-in anti-tamper mechanisms 
   (such as the Omahon Vanguard eBPF Shield) for the purpose of silently 
   monitoring users without their explicit, mathematically verifiable 
   consent.

